<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="89" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1999.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-12"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 12, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of the 21st
                            ultimo, No. 1370, relating a conversation between yourself and a Mr.
                            Holmes in regard to the Mexican bondholders.</p>
                        <p>I have to inform you in reply that the President does not think it
                            necessary to charge you with any duty connected with this subject.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c. &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>